  "prompt": "Can I get ob with CA intermediate?",
  "response": "Yes, you can pursue the CA Intermediate course after completing the **CA Foundation** (formerly known as CPT) or through the **Direct Entry** route. Here's how:\n\n### 1. **After CA Foundation**:\n   - If you have completed the CA Foundation exam (the entry-level exam for the CA course), you can register for CA Intermediate.\n   - You need to clear both groups of CA Foundation to proceed to CA Intermediate.\n\n### 2. **Direct Entry Route**:\n   - If you are a graduate or post-graduate with at least 55% marks in commerce or 60% marks in non-commerce streams, you can directly register for CA Intermediate without appearing for CA Foundation.\n   - Similarly, candidates who have passed the Intermediate level of ICSI or ICWAI can also directly register for CA Intermediate.\n\n### Steps to Register for CA Intermediate:\n1. Register with the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI).\n2. Complete 8 months of study period after registration.\n3. Enroll for the CA Intermediate exam.\n\n### Exam Structure:\nCA Intermediate consists of **two groups**, each with 4 papers. You can choose to appear for one group or both groups in one attempt.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you need more details!",
